http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Innovative-products-on-display/article13976260.ece

Innovative products developed by the CSIR-CFTRI will be demonstrated on January 4. Union Minister for Science and Technology and Earth Sciences Harsh Vardhan will visit the pavilion at CFTRI. The products that will be demonstrated include Neera in PET bottles; sugarcane juice; sugarcane juice crusher; carbonated fruit juices; quinoa, teff and chia-based food products; turmeric powder; tomato preservation; solar dehydrated products; kokum candy; gluten-free products; gelatine from fish waste; pectin from mango peel; staple food for disaster relief operations; milk carotenoid detection kit; mini dhal mill; kakra-making machine; dosa-making machine, and spouted bed roaster.